issue.description:
Have a look at the type declaration for MONTH_IN_YEAR in the long
	form of ISO 10303-203AM1 (WG3N916) (same in the IS pdf-file):
	  TYPE month_in_year_number = INTEGER;
	  WHERE
	    wr1: ((1 <= SELF) AND (SELF <= 12));
	  END_TYPE; -- month_in_year_number

	The same type is declared in ISO 10303-41:1994 as:

	  TYPE month_in_year_number = INTEGER;
	  WHERE
	    WR1: { 1 <= SELF <= 12 };
	  END_TYPE;

	AP214 uses this latter declaration as well.

	Semantically the two types are equal. However, should they not also be
	syntactically identical?

